cat << EOF
PHP is a widely-used Open Source general-purpose 
scripting language that is especially suited for 
Web development and can be embedded into HTML.
Its syntax draws upon C, Java, and Perl, 
and is easy to learn.
PHP runs on many different platforms and can be 
used as a standalone executable or as a module 
under a variety of Web servers.
It has excellent support for databases, XML, 
LDAP, IMAP, Java, various Internet protocols, 
and general data manipulation, and is extensible 
via its powerful API.
EOF
